<percentage>0</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum></teachingTypesInCurriculumYear></programCurriculum><programDescriptions><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Social Theory and Public Affairs allows students to develop a grasp of social theory and public affairs, their symbiosis and their role in the modern world. It focuses on a social sciences approach to issues in public affairs, working on the assumption that the practical challenges encountered public service and theories developed in academic work in social sciences should be mutually informing.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>objectives</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Capita Selecta Social Theory; Social Theory and Public Affairs; Active Citizenship; European Labour Markets and Employment Relations, Globalisation of Culture and Media; Sexuality, Ethnicity and Class; Social Interventions; Sociology of Religion; Theorising Gender; Urban Neighbourhoods and Communities; World Cities; Research Methods; Thesis.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>curriculum</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Seminars, lectures, audiovisual presentations, essays.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>instruction modes</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[It focuses specifically on social sciences approach to issues in public affairs, working on the assumption that the practical challenges encountered public service and the theories developed in academic work in the social sciences should be mutually informing. The historical and comparative dimensions emphasised in the majority of the courses train students to analyse public affairs issues from a fundamentally interdisciplinary perspective, and and to locate them in various sociological, political and cultural contexts. 

The Master's programme in Social Theory and Public Affairs is a flexible programme. Students can increase the interdisciplinarity of their programme by taking electives from other related programmes at the ISHSS. The University of Amsterdam is a major international centre for research in the social sciences, and many of the lecturers in the Master's programme are researchers at the Amsterdam School for Social science Research (ASSR). In particular, the ASSR's ‘Institutions, Inequalities and Internationalisation' research cluster houses researchers whose work deals with issues in social theory and public affairs. ]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[It focuses specifically on social sciences approach to issues in public affairs, working on the assumption that the practical challenges encountered public service and the theories developed in academic work in the social sciences should be mutually informing. The historical and comparative dimensions emphasised in the majority of the courses train students to analyse public affairs issues from a fundamentally interdisciplinary perspective, and and to locate them in various sociological, political and cultural contexts. 

